<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
(1) I can turn the television off, or change the channel..  the TV does not turn itself back on and chase me through the house until I hear its entire message.  (I watch very little Television anyhow).<br>
<br>
(2) The Mailman doesn't fish the flyer out of the garbage and kick in the front door repeatedly until I read it.  I can just toss it out of my sight.  And to be honest, television and snailmail adds do not seem as intrusive to me since I have the option ignore them as I please.<br>
<br>
(3) This form of marketing is a base form of harassment, they WILL NOT LEAVE YOU ALONE.  No matter if you have filed with a state program that is supposed to ban you from their calling list, no matter how polite, vicious, pleading or downright nasty you are, the same people will continue to call you over and over and over again.  I belong to a lobby here that has been fighting to ban unsolicited phone sales (and if I have my way, political and paid charitable solicitation) from being allowed to contact you without you signing up for it.<br>
<br>
I can stand door to door sales better then telemarketing,  at least they have the balls to face the possibly ANGRY day sleeper that they wake up.<br>
<br>
(4) no, you are incorrect. I can indeed hate only that form of promotion.  Spam mail is a close second, but I can filter most of it out.<br>
